1. Unicast
•	Data is sent from a single source to a single destination.
•	Example: One computer sending a message directly to another computer.   

2.Broadcast
•	Data is sent from one source to all devices in a network.
•	Every device in the network receives the data, even if they don’t need it.
•	Example: ARP Request (Address Resolution Protocol) – A router asks, “Who has this IP address?” and all devices in the network receive the request.
•	Ex:hub 

3.Multicast
•	Data is sent from one source to a specific group of devices in a network.
•	Only devices that are part of the multicast group receive the data.
•	Example: Live Streaming or Video Conferencing – A server streams video to selected subscribers instead of all network devices.
•	Ex:switch 
